# SeekerSim development standards

Read [docs/DEVELOPMENT.md](../../docs/DEVELOPMENT.md) before writing or reviewing code.

## Pacing

- Follow [docs/LEARNING_ROADMAP.md](../../docs/LEARNING_ROADMAP.md) — one phase or sub-step at a time.
- Propose the **smallest testable slice** before large implementations.
- Do not skip phases (e.g. no tracking before single-image detect works).
- Minimal diffs; no drive-by refactors or speculative features.

## Learning-oriented code

- Every new `pub fn` / `pub struct`: doc comment with summary, args, returns.
- Add optional `# C# analogy` for non-obvious Rust concepts.
- Prefer clarity over cleverness.

## Architecture (strict)

- **lib + bin**: thin `main.rs`, logic in `seeker_sim` library modules.
- **Module deps**: `api → pipeline → services → domain`; `domain` must NOT depend on axum, ort, or api.
- New features go in the module named in [docs/ARCHITECTURE.md](../../docs/ARCHITECTURE.md) — not in `main.rs`.
- HTTP only in `api/routes/`; ML only in `vision/`; types in `domain/`.
- Use `tracing` (not `println!`), `thiserror` + `Result` at boundaries.

## Before finishing a task

- `cargo test` and `cargo build` when Rust code changed.
- Update ARCHITECTURE / TOOLS / DECISIONS if layout or deps changed.
- Before push: [rules.md](../../rules.md) and pre-push security rule.

## Git

- Work on `dev`; merge to `master` via PR only.
